\intbl \ql \b Summary of Evaluator Report\b0 \line The evaluator indicated that the programme meets the minimum requirements in terms of all the relevant Criteria to be assessed and recommended that the programme be accredited.\line \line The programme is aligned to the institutional strategic objectives and has a strong managerial focus pitched at the appropriate NQF level 8.  The programme targets employees and entrepreneurs in the Hospitality industry.  Programme design emphasises e-learning empowering students to assume a greater responsibility for their own learning\'2C and a budget has been provided for the development of e-learning classrooms.  \line \line The curriculum is described in sufficient detail and makes adequate provision for developing the required research skills at a more advanced level.  Sufficient time is allocated for the Teaching and Learning Strategy to be followed.  The Institution has a suitable policy for the development of learning material. Suitable articulation pathways for this programme have been provided.\line \line Student admission criteria are clear and aligned with statutory requirements.  Provision is made for widening access by providing for RPL using the institutional policy.  The initial intake is capped at 30 per annum and students are ranked according to the ranking system developed.  The growth in student numbers is realistic with a target market of persons employed in the hospitality sector.  The institution provides for both full-time and part-time classes to be offered to cater for designated groups.  The draft Programme Handbook provides all the necessary information students may require.\line \line As this is a public Institution\'2C Criteria 3\'2C 4\'2C 7 and 8 are deemed to be in place.\line \line The institutional policy on teaching and learning is student-centred and aims at promoting active student learning\'2C which is appropriate to the programme demands and reflects the desired graduate attributes.  The programme will employ a range of teaching approaches supported by e-learning and the learning materials will be available on the learning platform.  Each student will have a supervisor providing guidance for the completion of the Research Report. Student support starts with an orientation session aimed at informing students about programme demands and outcomes\'2C and the institutional support available.  Student progress will be monitored and remedial action initiated where required.\line \line The Assessment Strategy is appropriate and is supported by the institutional Assessment Policy.   The types and number of assessment opportunities for each module is well described and provides for formative feedback.  Provision is made for both internal and external moderation as per the institutional Assessment Policy.\line \line The Directorate notes that the institution has included a Research Methods and Design\'E2\'80\'99 module \'2812 credits\'29 as well as an \'E2\'80\'98Applied Business Project\'E2\'80\'99 module \'2816 credits\'29 are included in the programme along with learning outcomes linked to research.  It is also mentioned in section 5.2 of the submission that the research- based modules will develop the ability of students to conduct independent studies\'2C gather information independently\'2C and to communicate the findings of their independent endeavours. It is stated that - each student will be allocated a supervisor\'2C who will provide the requisite guidance to enable the student to complete a research report. The submission further states that in the \'E2\'80\'9CApplied Business Project\'E2\'80\'9D module the supervisor will continuously reassess the module\'2C until he\'2Fshe is satisfied that the Research Report is of an acceptable standard to be submitted for external moderation\'2Fexamination. However\'2C the submission does not include information for Criterion 9. More information is needed regarding the research component of the programme\'2C its supervision and management as there are also learning outcomes that refer to research.\line \line The Directorate recommends that the programme be accredited with a condition.\cell \pard 

